title: What Does Admin Mean in My Account Settings
chunk_text: Every Amstat subscriber has an admin or primary contact on their account. The admin has the ability to make decisions for the account as well as manage some of the account settings for the entire subscription.

metadata.topic: Role and Responsibilities of the Account Admin

title: What Does Admin Mean in My Account Settings
chunk_text: Within the settings under 'My Account' and then 'Account Subscriptions', there is a list of subscribed users. Whether there is one account license or multiple, the word 'admin' will appear next to the person's name. This admin is the same as the primary account holder.

metadata.topic: Locating Admin Designation in Account Subscriptions

title: What Does Admin Mean in My Account Settings
chunk_text: The admin has the ability to turn on sharing features, download user activity reports, and upload company logos. They also have the authority to make overall changes to the account.

metadata.topic: Admin Permissions and Account Management Capabilities

title: What Does Admin Mean in My Account Settings
chunk_text: If an account admin or primary contact needs to be updated, please reach out to service@amstatcorp.com for assistance.

metadata.topic: Procedure for Updating Account Admin or Primary Contact
